 =?UTF-8?q?xperimental)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Final phase of the voice-messages epic (#120), all gated behind
experimentalAudioPlayerControls (off = today's recorder, unchanged). The
getUserMedia + ScriptProcessorNode -> real-time LAME MP3 pipeline is
preserved (no MediaRecorder: iOS can't play Chrome's Opus/WebM).

- Pause/resume while recording: a gate in onaudioprocess stops feeding the
  encoder, so resuming continues into the SAME encoder and yields one
  contiguous MP3. The timer banks only active time (pure TimerState helper,
  no per-tick slop); the live waveform freezes while paused. The mic stream
  stays live while paused (ponytail: OS indicator stays on; upgrade path
  track.enabled).
- Preview before send: stopping a recording shows the draft in the shared
  custom player (blob: URL; peaks work via fetch, position persistence is
  skipped for ephemeral blob: srcs at the store level) with send /
  record-again / discard. Send drafts exactly like the old checkmark.
- Press-and-hold gestures: hold the mic to record, release to preview;
  slide left past 80px to cancel, up past 60px to lock hands-free (then
  tap-to-stop + pause available). A quick tap (<300ms) still toggles like
  today, so both styles work. Pure classifyGesture() with mocha coverage;
  pointer events + capture, no long-press context menu.
- Original-audio toggle in the recorder UI (voiceRecordingOriginalAudio
  desktop setting, default off): requests noiseSuppression/echoCancellation/
  autoGainControl off — advisory, so the actual track.getSettings() are read
  back and unsupported setups say so instead of pretending.

Constraints honesty and gesture thresholds are unit-tested (27 passing
across the audio suites). The contiguous-MP3 invariant needs a live WebAudio
pipeline, so it's verified by the screenshot/e2e harness, not the unit suite.

Review hardening (adversarial pass):
- Abortable start: onRecordingStart is async (permission await before the mic
  opens). A generation counter (bumped on cancel/stop and each new start) is
  snapshotted at entry and re-checked after every await and before opening the
  mic, so a gesture that cancels/stops during the await can't resume and
  re-open the mic against intent, and a double pointerdown can't leave two
  MicRecorders; if getUserMedia resolves after being superseded, the fresh
  stream is stopped.
- Context menu is now suppressed for the whole gesture via a window-level
  listener (the mic button — and its onContextMenu — unmounts ~100ms into a
  hold, before the ~500ms OS long-press), removed in the gesture cleanup.
- The gesture's window listeners are also torn down on unmount (cleanup kept
  in a ref, invoked from the unmount effect), not only on pointerup/cancel.
- Locale keys: renamed our lock_recording -> slide_up_to_lock (it collided
  with upstream's translated "Lock Recording" and the untranslated merge would
  have shadowed it) and dropped our slide_to_cancel duplicate in favour of the
  translated chat_record_slide_to_cancel.
- Preview: focus lands on Send (the input is unmounted while previewing, so
  focusMessageInput was a no-op); the preview element and the shared voice
  singleton now pause each other so they can't sound at once.
